Products.ShortDescription: Original WWII German M35 helmet with liner, well-preserved condition, authentic battlefield collectible.
Products.FullDescription: This authentic WWII German M35 helmet features its original paint and partial decal, with the inner leather liner still intact. Manufactured circa 1939–1940, the helmet was widely used by the German Wehrmacht during the Second World War. It shows signs of field use but has been preserved in excellent collectible condition. A must-have for serious military history enthusiasts and collectors of WWII memorabilia.

Products.ShortDescription: 12th-century style chainmail hauberk, authentic medieval armor used by knights and infantry.
Products.FullDescription: This chainmail hauberk is an original medieval defensive armor piece, composed of thousands of interlinked iron rings. It provided excellent protection against swords and arrows while maintaining flexibility. Originating from the 12th century, this piece shows evidence of historical use but remains in strong condition. A significant addition for serious collectors of medieval warfare relics.

Products.ShortDescription: Brass-fronted cuirass used by French heavy cavalry during the Napoleonic Wars.
Products.FullDescription: This authentic French Napoleonic cuirass was worn by heavy cavalry (Cuirassiers) under Emperor Napoleon Bonaparte. Crafted with a steel backplate and polished brass front, this protective armor was both functional and symbolic of elite cavalry units. It bears regimental rivets and shows signs of use. A rare piece of 19th-century European military history.

Products.ShortDescription: Curved single-edged saber carried by French cavalry officers during the Napoleonic Wars.
Products.FullDescription: This elegant cavalry saber dates to the Napoleonic era, with a curved steel blade, brass hilt, and leather-bound grip. Designed for devastating slashing attacks from horseback, sabers were the primary weapon of French light cavalry. This piece shows battle wear consistent with age but retains excellent blade structure and craftsmanship. A premium acquisition for collectors of early 19th-century weaponry.
Products.Material: Steel blade, Brass hilt, Leather grip

Products.ProductName: British Brown Bess Flintlock Musket (19th Century)
Products.ShortDescription: British Army Brown Bess flintlock musket, standard infantry firearm of the Napoleonic era.
Products.FullDescription: The Brown Bess was the legendary smoothbore musket carried by British infantry from the 18th century through the Napoleonic Wars. This example, dated circa 1800, features an original walnut stock, iron barrel, and brass trigger guard. Known for its role at Waterloo and other major battles, it remains one of the most iconic military firearms of the 19th century.
Products.Manufacturer: British Ordnance Factory, Tower of London
